comment.narrative:
Component 1
Assisting the Government of Kazakhstan in the implementation of the obligations of the Stockholm Convention:
Inventory of new and unintentionally produced persistent organic pollutants (POPs);
National Implementation Plan update (in terms of POPs);
Capacity building of laboratories in POPs analysis;
Raising awareness of the impact of POPs.

Component 2
An initial evaluation of the mercury situation in the country;
Draft National Mercury Reduction Plan (National Plan of Implementation of the convention) was prepared and submitted to the Gvernment (Ministry of Energy of RK).

Component 3
Reduction of emissions of u POPs from incineration of healthcare waste through replacing incinerators by alternative equipment and creating Healthcare Waste Management Centers (six) in the pilot regions;
Capacity building of the medical staff on the treatment of healthcare waste and its treatment by autoclaving (150 people). 

Component 4: 
publication of the project results in the media;
project mid-term evaluation.

Component 1
Inventory of uPOPs releases (dioxins and furans, HCB, PCB and pentachlorbenzol) in accordance with the UNEP Guidance, and: 
Sources of database of POPs and uPOPs were prepared for the conduction of further inventarization of POPs and POPs; 
Conduction of assessment of industrial use of new POPs and available chemical and not chemical alternates;
Draft National Implementation Plan to implement obligations of the Stockholm Convention was prepared;
The methods of dioxins and furans are developed in the objects of environment (soil,water, air) in the type of National Standards of the Republic of Kazakhstan, which was adopted  by Committee of Technical Regulation and Meteorology of the Ministry of investment and development dated from  26.11.2016 №270 (ST RK 2813-2016);
Seminars and trainings were held in pilot regions, as well as in Aktau and Kyzylorda in order to raise awareness on POPs impacts;
As a result of project implementation, awareness of 300 staff of governmental bodies, industrial enterprises and NGOs were raised;
To create online courses, testing questions/answers were prepared for a training program on POPs issues capacity building.  

Component 2
Initial inventory of mercury was conducted in accordance to UNEP methods. The project conducted the investigations on mercury content in environment and in the people’s organism. By investigation objects were chosen water surface, fish and soil in Balkhash, Ust-Kamenogorsk, Kostanay cities as well as the hair of population of abovementioned cities.
The National Plan on reduction of mercury use and collection was prepared and submitted to the consideration of Authorized Governmental body.

Component 3
Equipment required for the Centers of Healthcare Waste Treatment was purchased and delivered. 
150 people were trained within the projects events.

Component 4
Articles: “Minamata Convention on mercury. Risks and possibilities for Kazakhstan”, magazine “Ecology and industry of Kazakhstan” № 1 (49) 2016. “

