1. With the aim of expansion of the representativeness of desert ecosystems, including the mountaineous subtype of deserts within the PAs system, a consultant has held meetings with local people and decision-makers of 6 districts of Almaty region for establishment of the Arganaty sanctuary and Ile-Balkash reserve. Approval of the decision-makers (at the level of the government of Almaty region) was obtained regarding creation of the wildlife corridor and Arganaty sanctuary; 
2. In line with the goals on assessment of the existing management practice of conservation institutions, identification of correlation between key values of PAs and PA management processes, the PA management effectiveness evaluation methodology was developed. 12 PAs and effectiveness of activities of Altyn Yemel National Park were evaluated as per the METT methodology; 
3. The hired mammalogy expert has prepared the analytical report on the state of key migratory animal species populations and the Action Plan on migratory animal species populations management for implementation of the Programme on migratory animal species populations management in Ile-Balkhash project area;  
4. The review of existing educational programmes has been prepared with the aim to introduce training programmes for students. Project proposals are being prepared to introduce environmental awareness programmes in project areas. 
5. Functional Zonation Atlases were prepared and issued in Kazakh and Russian languages for Ile-Balkhash and Aral-Syrdaria project areas for raising awareness of landscape approach principles
6. 6 grant projects on sustainable agriculture and 2 projects on combating with shifting sands were implemented. As a result, over 20 000 ha of desert pastures are sustainably managed and supplied with water. Living conditions of over 40 people (herders living in the remote rural area) were improved. Mechanical (laying down reed mats) and revegetation (planting of seedlings of hardy-shrub species) works wer

