2.	The PA Performance Measuring Methodology was approved by the Ministry of Agriculture’s Forestry and Wildlife Committee as the major document to assess performance of nature protection institutions at national level; 
3.	Standard training modules of learning programmes were approved by the Ministry of Agriculture’s Forestry and Wildlife Committee as a staff development tool at the systemic level
4.	The experience of applying phytomeliorative and mechanical methods of sand stabilizations was demonstrated in the 3 ha range. As a result, 40 000 seedlings of drought-resilient species were planted in pilot sites and more than 100 people of local communities from 2 project villages were taught how to combat shifting sands;
5.	Programmes and teaching materials on environmental education were developed for 4 pilot schools.  The work regarding equipping school laboratories with facilities  was carried out. Introduction of the environmental education programme will be finalized in 2018;  
6.	 The main part of the work was done to improve a recreation area in Ile-Balkhash project area. 40 unemployed women were trained in making felt, sewing and manufacturing souvenir products. Demonstration of the ecological tourism model created will be finalized in 2018;   
7.	 A biological background report on reintroduction of kulans of the Altyn Yemel SNNP in other historical habitats was prepared and approved by the Ministry of Agriculture’s Forestry and Wildlife Committee. Kulan reintroduction was included in the 2018-2020 National Programme for conservation and recovery of kulan populations;     
